Name: The Tam
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Kasey Draper', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115077542804382537927/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJyt1mG0kZ5Nozsf2-nMREg5G2IZ5hrdWcY5AhHr=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Worth the read. We were walking around and celebrating my little sisters 21st birthday. Attempted to go into this place and the “security guard” wouldn’t let her in on her 21st birthday. Claiming that she “could have been born at 11:59pm today” meaning she wouldn’t actually be 21 until the minute she was born, or the following day. Myself and my husband are clearly over 21, not that it even matters. We tried to tell the man, it’s her 21st birthday, today. He let in countless other people, without question or ID, while examining each of our government issued IDs and embarrassed us, and turned us away for no reason. This is no popular or famous place that we would make an extreme attempt to get in, it’s a random bar that we walked past. The lack of professionalism and sheer lack of capacity to read the date on a government issued ID was both embarrassing and unnecessary. He felt the need to ridicule us, by letting others in, after us, without question. We were not rude, or unfriendly by any means. We asked the man how is night was going. Only to be turned away based on his lack of reading or misinterpretation of a government issued ID. He told other members of the staff that we were misrepresenting ourselves which is untrue. We had countless positive experiences at other bars in the area. This is the one and only negative experience we had. Which is saying something about the “guard” and the staff at this establishment. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'James Zimmardi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110216387688754787622/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgZuNATtWAMAfkZc-Pm-yDX9_FVvJRJiFJkwWR4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': "There are not enough great things to say about The Greatest Bar as it is appropriately named. I've been going there over 15 years before and after Celtics and Bruins games and concerts at TD Garden.

Having been a staple patron that is well known by staff and management over the years TGB has always treated me great personally. But typically the staff treats all their patrons great.

4 levels of different Bars each with its own feel, you can find a floor that suits you. Level one is the sports bar with one HUGE screen and smaller screens for different games. Level One has had bands playing live music too. Level two is the loft bar overlooking Level one. Level three has its own bar and some games and Level Four has the larger room with tables, a Red rope area for private parties and sometimes has a DJ or live band.

The drinks are always awesome. Best Long Island Iced Teas ever. The food is also good.

TGB really is THE GREATEST BAR.", 'time': 1653536895}, {'author_name': 'Joe Young', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106220242837889780438/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxjpz_uXAazkdwP6yGpNXmI2Tdjj_usINplv2EY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': "I went to a lot of bars in Boston, and this place was easily the worst. Clearly not the best bar in pyongyang yet alone Boston. I was there for the Frozen Four as they decided to host two teams fan bases for the pregame party, except they weren't prepared. Like at all. It was bad, 20 minutes between drinks, surley staff, just plain bad. I get you were overwhelmed but we tipped much better than we should have, and you threatened to shank me (the customer) for having the audacity to expect a drink in under 30 minutes. Personally, I blame the management not the bartender. It was my first day in Boston so I put up with it, but yikes. Go a block over to Sully's where they are prepared, the drinks flow, and no one threatens to kill you and the real Boston fans go. We talked to so many locals who said avoid after the fact, and they were right.

So many better options close to TD Garden, why subject yourself to this place.

Name: Durty Nelly's
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Emily Zambrano', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115303729052125658200/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJzuYebOFmkvVDW3av686OLDSqX3q2MyFXqhzjyY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'My sister and I went to this bar upon recommendation. If I could give it a 0/5 I would. I am a server and my sister is a bartender. So we know about the service industry. Here, there was a shortage of everything, but mostly respect. We got to the bar, ordered and received our drinks. At the moment in which we decided to go to the restroom, there were no other women in the bar so we saw best that we accompany each other. While we were in the restroom, a group of boys arrived at the bar. Once we returned to our seats the bartender told us that we couldn’t go into the restroom together (understandable for men, not so much for women). But we apologized and assured the bartender that we just wouldn’t use the restroom again.  Then, one of the boys at the bar threw ice at my sister. The bartender did nothing, let him stay. Another patron was the one to say something to the guy that threw the ice. Again, the bartender saw everything. My sister and I decided to leave. It is NOT okay to treat women or ANYONE like this. When I called the establishment my call was answered by the same bartender who claimed he had already “spoken” to these boys, and immediately hung up on me - and didn’t answer the other times I called to discuss this issue. I can’t believe that people still act like this and I truly can’t fathom the fact that nothing was addressed in that moment. This entire experience was absolutely disappointing and disgusting.', 'time': 1648019266}, {'author_name': 'Chad McDonald', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118190604656363676360/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJz8wMdjpGbWPuu8vNh5pAb1W1YcQuqJL2uw2sjT=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Best hole in the wall there is in Boston. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Annabelle Critz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118079058549277288204/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjdzujVH51FBO7GEOMiPNCkXSDqUwGpsEpbtvqfVg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'I went in last night with one of my girlfriends, hoping to listen to some of the live music, which was fantastic. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Andrew Cruz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108738348586127069938/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiGw4FVrlpDr9RYSODKluPKjCU-BmWVzWBEMYSRWFs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'I’d first like to start off with the positives! We received amazing service from a very friendly staff and the atmosphere was great. We ordered drinks, Buffalo wings, and tried to order the Belgian fries because they sound amazing. The drinks were excellent, but unfortunately the wings were a miss and we unintentionally ordered just a side of fries. I asked our server if these were the Belgian fries, and our server said he would get them. Once we received the fries, they were identical to the side of fries with a side of three dips. The menu said they would be twice fried crispy shoestrings and they certainly didn’t live up to that description. Before we left we saw some burgers that looked amazing, so it’s very possible we just didn’t order the best of the menu. I would say overall the drinks and service were very good, but the food left a lot to be desired.', 'time': 1645828179}, {'author_name': 'Matt S', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110563420603076505006/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJx4JhlknBdg_sptd-Nmc0nUNAl7FjE7A_9DYMOT8w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'Went before a show at the garden to get dinner and drinks before. Place was moderately busy but not crazy once we got there. I never like to dock stars on service alone (especially with a worker shortage at the moment) but the attitude of every employee we came across was totally unacceptable and uncalled for. We had 2 disabled/ visually impaired people in our party and when they forgot one of their drinks, all I got was a sigh and an eye roll. Same thing when our food came… they just threw random food on the table as it was a different person then took our order and after we had watched her try to give it to 3 other tables. Then the bill came and one of them asked to split it (which I understand we should’ve asked before hand) and she immediately started yelling at us so we nicely said it’s our fault and not a big deal and said we’d just use 1 card. She came back with the check and was still annoyed that we paid with only one card even though she berated us for implying we’d do the opposite. I haven’t tipped under 20% since the pandemic because I know this industry has been hit hard but this was completely uncalled for and it wasn’t even that busy/ early enough that they’d already all be in a bad mood. We ended up leaving early and going to the show early and paying for drinks inside the garden cause we felt so unwanted here.

The apps were great and burgers were good. That being said I’d go back if it weren’t for the service. reviews:

Nick, Colin  and Justin and the rest of the crew always go out of their way to make me feel comfortable and welcome even though I am not running up a huge bill.  Both E.J. and Dave were also outstanding and although I met Chelsea only once, she did an excellent job.

The hotel is lucky to have these people on their payroll representing it to the public in a city with so many nice places to go.

My colleagues (very real) New Jersey ID was suspected by the bartender as “fake”. They seized it, and refused to return it. After the police were called, they cut the ID before police could arrive. They then denied this, and the ID was not presented to police (which, correct me if I'm wrong, is knowingly destroying evidence). Fries were good but pulled pork was super fatty and the wings were grisly—just not a great flavor. Run of the mill mozz sticks. Salad was decent.

They don’t have a drinks menu (weird for a sports bar) which wouldnt be the end of the world if the waitress actually knew what was in the drinks. I specifically asked if the drink she recommended had pineapple juice (due to a mild pineapple allergy) and she said no. When it came out to me, I immediately felt the tell tale sting on my tongue that gave away the pineapple. The drink was probably was 80% pineapple juice and 2% alcohol.

Also, none of the waitresses were wearing masks—not even when they brought the food out.

They overcharged us for an item when we finally asked for the check and we had to get our check corrected. When they brought it back after the correction, they double taxed us -once for the total on the original receipt, and a second time for the total on the credit card receipt (the total of which included the original tax). Had to have a back and forth before they realized the mistake.

+3 for mediocre food
-1 for allergy mishap/poor service
